<h2><b>Wood Lockers will keep your sports equipment Dry and clean!</b></h2>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Most sports are a rough and tumble activity and cuts and bruises are just part of the game. A simple abrasion is not a big deal unless it gets infected. Did you know that there are millions of potentially harmful germs that can get inside that cut and create a potentially harmful infection? A simple way to prevent an infection is to keep your sports equipment clean and dry.</span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">There are germs everywhere, but the place germs thrive is in a hot, moist environment. One of the best places germs love to live in is a hot, sweaty sports bag. If your sports equipment is left inside a air tight bag, it becomes a breeding ground for these potentially harmful germs. There are some really simple ways to prevent germs from spreading:</span>

&nbsp;
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Disinfection</span></h3>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">A simple disinfectant spray after practice or the game will kill 90% of the germs on contact. Here is a blog post on <a href="http://customsportslockers.com/2017/04/25/athletic-lockers-disinfection/">wood locker</a> disinfection we did on making a healthy, simple spray that will keep your gear clean and ready to go for the next game.</span>

&nbsp;
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Wood Lockers</span></h3>
<img class="size-medium wp-image-693 alignright" src="http://customsportslockers.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/football-locker-mudroom-locker-300x200.jpg" alt="athletic locker football locker" width="300" height="200">

